	fibo-actus-act:hasParameterName "calendar" ;
	cmns-cls:isClassifiedBy fibo-actus-act:ACTUSContractTermGroup-Calendar ;
	cmns-dsg:hasDescription "Calendar defines the non-working days which affect the dates of contract events (CDE's) in combination with EOMC and BDC. Custom calendars can be added as additional enum options." ;
	cmns-dsg:hasTag "CLDR" ;
	cmns-dsg:hasTextualName "Calendar" ;
	.

fibo-actus-act:ACTUSContractTerm-CNTRL
	a
		owl:NamedIndividual ,
		fibo-actus-act:ACTUSContractTerm
		;
	rdfs:label "ACTUS dictionary term - CNTRL" ;
	rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://spec.edmcouncil.org/fibo/ontology/ACTUS/ACTUSContractTerms/> ;
	fibo-actus-act:hasParameterName "contractRole" ;
	cmns-cls:isClassifiedBy fibo-actus-act:ACTUSContractTermGroup-ContractIdentification ;
	cmns-dsg:hasDescription """CNTRL defines which position the CRID ( the creator of the contract record ) takes in a contract. For example, whether the contract is an asset or liability, a long or short position for the CRID. 

Most contracts are simple on or off balance sheet positions which are assets, liabilities. Such contracts can also play a secondary role as a collateral. 

The attribute is highly significant since it determines the direction of all cash flows. The exact meaning is given with each CT in the ACTUS High Level Specification document.""" ;
	cmns-dsg:hasTag "CNTRL" ;
	cmns-dsg:hasTextualName "Contract Role" ;
	.

fibo-actus-act:ACTUSContractTerm-CPID
	a
		owl:NamedIndividual ,
		fibo-actus-act:ACTUSContractTerm
		;
	rdfs:label "ACTUS dictionary term - CPID" ;
	rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://spec.edmcouncil.org/fibo/ontology/ACTUS/ACTUSContractTerms/> ;
	fibo-actus-act:hasParameterName "counterpartyID" ;
	cmns-cls:isClassifiedBy fibo-actus-act:ACTUSContractTermGroup-Counterparty ;
	cmns-dsg:hasDescription """CPID identifies the counterparty to the CRID in this contract.

CPID is ideally the official LEI which can be a firm, a government body, even a single person etc. However, this can also refer to a annonymous group in which case this information is not to be disclosed. CPID may also refer to a group taking a joint risk or more generally, CPID is the main counterparty, against which the contract has been settled.""" ;
	cmns-dsg:hasTag "CPID" ;
	cmns-dsg:hasTextualName "Counterparty Identifier" ;
	.

fibo-actus-act:ACTUSContractTerm-CRID
	a
		owl:NamedIndividual ,
		fibo-actus-act:ACTUSContractTerm
		;
	rdfs:label "ACTUS dictionary term - CRID" ;
	rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://spec.edmcouncil.org/fibo/ontology/ACTUS/ACTUSContractTerms/> ;
	fibo-actus-act:hasParameterName "creatorID" ;
	cmns-cls:isClassifiedBy fibo-actus-act:ACTUSContractTermGroup-ContractIdentification ;
	cmns-dsg:hasDescription """This identifies the legal entity creating the contract record. The counterparty of the contract is tracked in CPID.

CRID is ideally the official LEI which can be a firm, a government body, even a single person etc. However, this can also refer to a annonymous group in which case this information is not to be disclosed. CRID may also refer to a group taking a joint risk.""" ;
	cmns-dsg:hasTag "CRID" ;
	cmns-dsg:hasTextualName "Creator Identifier" ;
	.

fibo-actus-act:ACTUSContractTerm-CT
	a
		owl:NamedIndividual ,
